%% Customer registration-request → dealer approval → order — Daimler
%% Built on Merchant B2B Contracts (relation request → approval) + Merchant Product Restrictions.
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Cust as Customer<br/>(company user)
    participant Yves as Yves Storefront
    participant MRel as MerchantB2bContracts (Zed)
    participant MP as Merchant Portal<br/>(Dealer)
    participant Restrict as MerchantProductRestriction
    participant DB as MariaDB

    Note over Cust,DB: Customer must be in a dealer's approved pool before ordering

    Cust->>Yves: Submit registration request to dealer<br/>(business unit + owner + message)
    Yves->>MRel: create relation request (status Pending)
    MRel->>DB: persist request

    Note over MP,DB: Dealer reviews in "New customers" MP page
    MP->>MRel: approve / reject
    alt Approved
        MRel->>DB: relation created (approved) + merchant-specific customer ID
        MRel->>Restrict: apply per-customer product lists (allow/exclude)
        MP->>MRel: set merchant-specific prices / delivery costs / methods
    else Rejected
        MRel->>DB: request rejected (no relation)
    end

    Note over Cust,DB: Customer selects an active dealer
    Cust->>Yves: choose active dealer
    Yves->>Restrict: resolve visible products for (customer, dealer)
    Yves->>MRel: resolve merchant-specific prices
    Cust->>Yves: add to cart → checkout (Invoice only)
    Yves->>DB: place order (scoped to selected dealer/merchant)
